title: Bulgaria Coronavirus COVID-19 Vaccination Rate
description: The number of COVID-19 vaccination doses administered per 100 people in Bulgaria rose to 68 as of Nov 12 2022. Total number of vaccination doses administered per 100 people in the total population. This is counted as a single dose, and may not equal the total number of people vaccinated, depending on the specific dose regime (e.g. people receive multiple doses). This page includes a chart with historical data for Bulgaria Coronavirus Vaccination Rate.
author: Our World in Data
